Why don't you know the difference between flesh that had a soul and flesh that didn't ?
So ya know, flesh that seems to have fiber across it like fish or turkey, didn't seem to have a soul. As opposed to pig or squid or meat like "glazed ham". Cow liver reminds me of when I was too young to know the difference, my grandmother made "pork chops". I don't need to eat humans to guess it'd likely be the same. Some go completely vegetarian for not knowing the difference. Salmon type fish and the meat of turkeys is good enough for me.
This planet is depraved AND stupid
